Are you saying that the tangle of honeysuckle roots are on his side
and yours?  And it's like a viney tree?
If you trim back the vines they should resprout.  You might want to
just try a few first. If you trim it back too much all at once you
could kill the tree / vine.  It sounds like trimming it all back the
way you want might be too much for the plant.

As a short term fix you could plant some annual vines like sweet peas
or nasturtium to fill in the bare parts.

good luck
Laura
